tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE resource_utilization_metrics (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  resource_name VARCHAR(50),
  utilization_percentage FLOAT,
  efficiency_score FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE resource_utilization (id INT PRIMARY KEY,
resource_name STRING,
utilization_percent FLOAT,
efficiency_metric FLOAT)

CREATE TABLE performance_analysis (id INT PRIMARY KEY,
resource_id INT,
execution_time FLOAT,
query_time FLOAT)

CREATE TABLE efficiency_metrics (id INT PRIMARY KEY,
resource_id INT,
efficiency_score FLOAT,
efficiency_rating STRING)

CREATE TABLE resource_utilization_metrics (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    resource_name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    resource_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    utilization_percentage FLOAT NOT NULL,
    efficiency_score FLOAT NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE performance_analysis_metrics (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    analysis_date DATE NOT NULL,
    resource_id INT NOT NULL,
    performance_metric_name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    performance_value FLOAT NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE ResourceUtilizationMetrics (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    resource_name VARCHAR(255),
    resource_type VARCHAR(255),
    utilization_percentage FLOAT,
    efficiency_score FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE PerformanceAnalysis (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    resource_id INT,
    analysis_date DATE,
    performance_metric VARCHAR(255),
    metric_value FLOAT,
    FOREIGN KEY (resource_id) REFERENCES ResourceUtilizationMetrics(id)
);

CREATE TABLE ResourceDetails (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    resource_name VARCHAR(255),
    resource_type VARCHAR(255),
    location VARCHAR(255),
    owner VARCHAR(255)
);

CREATE TABLE UserMetrics (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INT,
    login_date DATE,
    sessions_count INT,
    duration_minutes INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES Users(id)
);
